title: For Trade:  DOCUMENTED FBI 1076 COMPLETE PACKAGE WITH RARE AMMO AND PROTOTYPE GRIP
postcontent: I purchased this FBI 1076 from a family friend who's husband had purchased it from S&W on buy back. The gun is in mint condition and was one of only three he saw come in from S&W with the Gold Bead front sight and plain black Novak rear sight while a agent with the FBI. The gun comes in the #s matching box with label stating it was shipped to the FBI Academy. The other end clearly states it was returned to S&W. Talked to Roy Jinks and he said it was made and shipped to the FBI in May of 1990 being one of the first. The pistol comes with 17 magazines and only two of them look like they have been used. Also comes with 17 new S&W magazine springs as well. Has all three grips with it. The FBI palm swell, curved, straight grip plus a prototype that S&W was working on at the time. The prototype is marked with "p" at the bottom there were very few of these ever made. Comes with one box of Federal XM100A the experimental load they were developing for the FBI. The rarest box is Winchester Western marked sample "C" restricted sales to law enforcement only that's the load that Winchester was trying to develop for the FBI before they finally gave up and let Federal have it. I talked to a Historian at Winchester and he said those were super rare and Winchester Western made very few boxes of them. The pistol will also come with 6 full boxes of Federal 10c Classic the load the FBI finally went with 180 grain HI-SHOCK JHP. The pistol comes with everything it did from S&W when it was shipped to the FBI, cleaning kit owners manual and warranty card. You want find another 1076 FBI package with what this one has. Please note: WILL ONLY TRADE FOR ITEMS LISTED BELOW! WILL NOT RESPOND TO CALL ME OR TEXT ME. IF YOU HAVE AN ITEM LISTED BELOW PLEASE BE SURE TO SEND PICTURES ON FIRST INQUIRY.WILL BE GLAD TO SEND MORE PICTURES ONCEYOUSEND TRADE ITEMS PICTURES. THANKS FOR LOOKING.

title: For Sale:  KELTEC KSG WITH EXTRAS!!!
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Keltec KSG Shotgun that includes original box and very few shells through it. Purchase will include Keltec KSG, Magpul Angled Foregrip, Sightmark Reflex sight(needs new batteries), and original box for keltec ksg.
The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".
This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

PRICE IS $850 only trades are something in 7MM or 300winmag bolt actions.

title: For Sale:  Arcteryx LEAF Echo Pack
postcontent:
This was bought for a deployment and used as a carry on only, no tactical or field use and only one 18 mile walk, it's only dusty from sitting in my garage. Arc'teryx stopped making this pack and they are highly sought after, they're selling on eBay for $400+.

It's the crocodile color and medium size so it will fit most, it's also extremely adjustable and the waist belt can be removed and adjusted up or down. The top pouch is removable and the bottom houses the lowering line attachments and straps for STRLLS if you want to jump the bag static line or MFF.

The pics of the bag on the steps are the actual bag, the other pics are just to show detail from the manufacture.

Intended for long operations and extended patrols Arc'teryx LEAF designed the Echo backpack to be tough, durable and fully loaded for any mission parameter. Featuring a tubular main compartment with a top lid eliminates failure points and increases durability. In addition, it allows longer, awkward gear and weaponry to be carried easily and comfortably. Features include hydration pocket, MOLLE compatible PALS, one large pocket and multiple strap management systems for a clean pack free of loose webbing. This true 3-day pack is outfitted with a thermoformed hipbelt and V-frame suspension for comfortable and effective weight distribution, decreasing pressure points and muscle fatigue so your endurance won't depend on your gear. For HALO/HAHO operations, the Echo has a simple and clean attachment system for the lowering line that eliminates the need for an additional drop bag or harness. The line is connected directly into the packs with high-strength, climbing-harness grade webbing.

Only trades considered would be knives, benchmade, zero tolerance, or towards a CRK, Hinderer, or Strider and I would pay the difference.
